Metadata-Version: 1.1
Name: pyclimenu
Version: 0.1.4
Summary: The easy way to create command line menus
Home-page: https://github.com/sp1thas/pyclimenu
Author: Panagiotis Simakis
Author-email: simakis@autistici.org
License: UNKNOWN
Download-URL: https://github.com/sp1thas/pyclimenu/archive/master.zip
Description: pyclimenu
        =========
        
        Install
        -------
        
        .. code:: bash
        
            $ pip install pyclimenu
        
        Demo
        ----
        
        .. code:: python
        
            >>> from pyclimenu import Menu
            >>> def first_function(a=0):
            ...     print(a*2)
            ...
            >>> def second_function(a=0):
            ...     print(a*4)
            ...
            >>> mn = Menu()
            >>> mn.add_item(label='first function', callback=first_function, params={'a': 2})
            >>> mn.add_item(label='second function', callback=second_function, params={'a': 1})
            >>> mn.display()
        
             [0] first function
             [1] second function
             [2] Exit
            Select option: > 1
            4
            >>>
        
        
Keywords: menu
Platform: UNKNOWN
